site_description_general: 10 m upstream of culvert inlet in pool. Too shallow to sample riffle soul sample top end of shallow pool. Right bank
150m downstream of culvert on Beaver FSR upstream of first beaver dam (from culvert downstream).
comments_field:
Due to shallow water depths in riffle sections sample was taken at shallow pool at the top and near where flow was entering. Two samples taken.          

Fish were observed downstream of the lowest beaver dam 500m from he Fraser River). Idea is to see if we detect fish upstream of dams but downstream of the FSR.

Filtering was extremely slow, so a second filter was taken and will need another row created in this attribute table for ds2b
Tme to 1.6L 346s

Took water quality again this morning because has been raining heavily so wanted to see if Lieuwen was evident through conductivity which it appears it is approximately 10% less conductivity which could impact detect ability.
